The Katsina State Government, has reviewed its COVID-19 order, saying Muslim faithful will hence forth be allowed to observe their Juma’at prayers which would be done inline with health/security guidelines. The Secretary to the Government of the State (SGS) Mustapha Mohammad Inuwa, made the announcement in a statement he issued, said the measure taken as directed by Governor Aminu Bello Masari, was the outcome of their deliberation with religious leaders, traditional rulers and security agencies in the state. He said, ” the suspension of Friday prayers has been lifted with immediate effect but to be conducted under some stipulated health/ security guidelines. “The Imams should however avoid prolonged sermons in order to discharge their followers within short period. ” The SGS further advised people to maintained and strictly adhere to all the rules and regulations provided by the health experts in fighting the pandemic.